            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/10–149</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Acting Secretary of
                        State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-01">October 1,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">China Blockade</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The President brought up of his own initiative the question of the handling of
                    the Isbrandtsen Line vessels by the Nationalist Government, and indicated
                    strongly, as he has previously indicated, that he wished the blockade to be
                    effective and that he desired the Department to do nothing to be of assistance
                    to these vessels. I informed him this was the position we were taking, with the
                    exception that we were warning the Nationalist Government not to bomb vessels
                    from the air when they carried American citizens. The President stressed again
                    the fact that his policy was to permit the blockade to work effectively, to
                    which policy he expected strict adherence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> E. <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
